                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 24354/4.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Monroe</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Jose</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-05-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 5, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Monroe reports destruction of Cartago by earthquake, during which it is
                    estimated that 500 persons were killed or wounded. Says court of peace was
                    destroyed. Reports that Americans are safe. Adds that San Jose was badly shaken,
                    but says no lives were lost.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
